This is called when `VInst` is the instruction *using* the value `V`. Wait, `VInst` is `dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)`.
Ah! `V` is the operand. `VInst` is the instruction that *produces* the value `V`.
Wait, `U` is the use. `I` is the instruction being simplified.
```cpp
